	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />If you want lots of features you could go with Nintendo MMC-5 for emulation as it's very flexible and powerful, although it doesn't have CHR-RAM technically though some emulators will give it that. Alternatively I recommend FME-7 (Sunsoft) which is mapper #069. 
<br />
<br />You mentioned more PRG-RAM, the MMC5 can have something like 32kb or 64kb of PRG-RAM maximum. You should really just look at mapper documents and find what you like.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


